### Coding standards
- Must follow C# coding standards
- Must use MVVM mode to ensure separation of view and logic
- Must use XAML to unify style
- For smaller components, you must use inline functions, but separate complex logic into code-behind or service classes
- If necessary, use dependency injection to manage services to reduce coupling between classes
- Please use WPF controls instead of WinForms controls
- The code must be unit tested to ensure its stability

### File organization
- Views/ directory contains all view files
- Styles/ directory contains global style definitions
- ViewModels/ directory contains corresponding view models
- Models/ directory contains data models
- Services/ directory contains business logic services
- App_csharp/ directory contains csharp dd driver call sample code
- Driver/ directory contains dd driver files

### Retrieval priority
1. *.xaml - XAML view file
2. *ViewModel.cs - view model file
3. *Service.cs - service class file
4. *.styles.xaml - Style file
5. App.xaml - Application configuration

### Keyword priority
- "KeyMapping" - Key mapping related
- "Sync" - Synchronization function related
- "Style" - Style definition
- "Service" - Service class
- "ViewModel" - View model
- "View" - View component